description.narrative: Greater resilience against the impact of the COVID-19 outbreaks achieved through the distribution of critical hygiene materials and age-appropriate and cultural-sensitive learning materials among 305,767 vulnerable people (164,016 children and 141,751 adults which includes 4,608 migrants and 533 children with disabilities) in affected communities.
